  "body": "Hi there,\r\n\r\nWe do see following issues related to this scenario:\r\n\r\n[https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/issues/14676](url)\r\n[https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/issues/14689](url)\r\n[https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/issues/18507](url)\r\n[https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/issues/16282](url)\r\n\r\nHowever, we couldnot figure out why the balance of our account still shows 0. Our local geth node seems to be synched %99 percent (84 blocks difference). We do see the transaction in the local geth node but the balance still shows zero. \r\n\r\nYour comments will be appreciated, thanks. \r\n\r\n#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: `1.8.21-stable-9dc5d1a9`\r\nOS & Version: Windows\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\n> eth.getBalance('0x80c752a410c23d34c12806bae68165721205e1f3')\r\nAbove function should return 0.001 \r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n\r\nLocal Synch Status of Rinkeby Testnet.\r\n\r\n> eth.syncing\r\n{\r\n  currentBlock: 3751470,\r\n  highestBlock: 3751554,\r\n  knownStates: 29371245,\r\n  pulledStates: 29367955,\r\n  startingBlock: 0\r\n}\r\n\r\nOur transaction is visible on geth.\r\n\r\n```json\r\n`> eth.getTransactionFromBlock('3748773', 1)\r\n{\r\n  blockHash: \"0x610035ef62e6fffc646bc6be9c12d211c50929af9f87193980bc7209b0f0cb51\r\n\",\r\n  blockNumber: 3748773,\r\n  from: \"0x08d13d527a19fc5203d2ce2e57c59036d6cafb6e\",\r\n  gas: 21000,\r\n  gasPrice: 6000000000,\r\n  hash: \"0xfdac6aa23c65c8742eb303c0d85bcdd3018c40da1e234c59f1fb8b4f57b418d6\",\r\n  input: \"0x\",\r\n  nonce: 22,\r\n  r: \"0x2bfb158db42ddf880be56d1330a6a67f41baa5fd1c45d69e19bbfbb40b46b4ca\",\r\n  s: \"0x54823ab0feb27528fcf7fb8a631c4337835f48e15cf4a1ef49a1aaf0e1da7745\",\r\n  to: \"**0x80c752a410c23d34c12806bae68165721205e1f3**\",\r\n  transactionIndex: 1,\r\n  v: \"0x2b\",\r\n  value: **1000000000000000**\r\n}`\r\n```\r\n\r\nHowever getBalance returns 0.\r\n\r\n`> eth.getBalance('0x80c752a410c23d34c12806bae68165721205e1f3')\r\n> 0   `\r\n\r\n\r\nLast Block returns 0. \r\n\r\n`> eth.getBlock(\"latest\").number\r\n0\r\n`\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n\r\n1. Start local geth node with following command\r\n `geth --rinkeby --rpc --rpcaddr \"127.0.0.1\" --datadir \"c/test\" console 2>> geth-personal.log`\r\n2. personal.newAccount()\r\n3. eth.accounts\r\n`> eth.accounts\r\n[\"**0x80c752a410c23d34c12806bae68165721205e1f3**\", \"0xe073ddffdb30439b696cf54ec2e1a7\r\n42d8ea1195\"]`\r\n4. Transfer 0.001 ETH to **0x80c752a410c23d34c12806bae68165721205e1f3**\r\n5. Check Block Number (3748773) received in local geth node\r\n6. eth.getTransactionFromBlock('3748773', 1)  We do see the transaction on local geth. \r\n7. eth.getBalance('0x80c752a410c23d34c12806bae68165721205e1f3') returns 0.\r\n\r\nUgur ACAR \r\nBlockchain Architect",
