    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "` %99 percent ` synced, in the case of a fast-synced, is not a correct estimate. What you're seeing is that all blocks up to the so called pivot point has been downloaded (the pivot point is at least 64 blocks behind head, and the head moves forward). Downloading all blocks is fairly quick, what takes time is downloading all the state entries. That's a much longer running job, and until you have the complete state, you will not get accurate information out of the client.  \r\n\r\nYou need to wait until the sync is 100% complete, or at least until the fast-sync is complete up to the pivot point: after that it will import the remaining (hundred or so) blocks that came after the pivot point.",
